<string name="a">A. The episode is characterized by either a mixture or a rapid alternation (i.e. within a few hours) of hypomanic, manic and depressive symptoms.</string>
<string name="b">B. Both manic and depressive symptoms must be prominent most of the time during a period of at least two weeks.</string>

